                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar divi Nervae <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Nerva Traianus <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Germ</abbr><ex>anicus</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> V <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> IIII <lb n="4"/>ob periculum cataractarum <lb n="5"/>derivato flumine tutam Da<lb break="no" n="6"/>nuvi navigationem fecit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Sogenannte Tabula Traiana. In mehrere Teile gebrochen. Datierung: 1.1. (Antritt des 4. Konsulats Trajans) bis 9.12.101 n. Chr. (Ende der 5. trib. pot.).</p>
